==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lodgeable
<hw>Lodge"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>logeable</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That may be or can be
lodged; <as>as, so many persons are not <ex>lodgeable</ex> in this
village</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Capable of affording lodging; fit for lodging
in.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧ The <xex>lodgeable</xex> area of the
earth.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Jeffrey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lodged</ent>⟦br⟧
